Solution. \[\begin{equation*}
        \int dx_1\int dx_2e^{-\frac{3}{2}\left(x_1^2+x_2^2\right)+x_1x_2}=\frac{\pi}{\sqrt{2}}
    \end{equation*}\]
It is clear that the exponent can be written in the form

\begin{equation*}
    \begin{pmatrix}
        x_1 & x_2
    \end{pmatrix}
    \begin{pmatrix}
        -\frac{3}{2} & \frac{1}{2}\\
